@node "new" ".-^†Whats new in v1.1 ?†^-."
@next "introduction"
@prev "main"
@{b}@{u} What's new in this version? @{ub}@{uu}

* Fixed some ASNI bugs (reported by zod)
* Improved the documentation
* Enforcer tested

@endnode
@node "introduction" ".-^†INTRODUCTION†^-."
@next "how2"
@prev "new"
@{b}@{u} Megapager Introduction @{ub}@{uu}

Megapager is just another pager door. But unlike most other pagers it
also includes the posibility for the sysop to choose how he wants to
start the chat, and the text will be written at the beginning of the
chat with a writer. In other words this pager door also comes with a
built-in chatter.

@{b}@{u} Features: @{ub}@{uu}

* Highly Configurable
* Support for Sysop_Away message
* If page was not successful the user can leave a comment

@{b}@{u} Requirements: @{ub}@{uu}
 
    - FAME BBS v 1.25+
    - MUI for the config-editor to work
    - BGUI.library for the pager-gui to work.



 
                            @{"†BACK 2 MAINMENU†" link "main" 0}
@endnode

@node "how2" ".-^†How to use†^-."
@next "install"
@prev "introduction"
@{b}@{u} How does it work? @{ub}@{uu}

Fist the door will check to see if sysop is set away, and if so if the user has access to override 
the chat flag and page sysop anyway. If not he will be asked if he wants to leave a Comment.

If the user is not set away the following will happen:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
When the user first starts the pager it will ask him for a reson (if this is ON in the cfg)

Then the page will start and a window will pop up on sysop's frontmost screen 
(or WB if the frontmost screen is not a public screen)

The user can break the page-process by hitting any key.

The sysop has the following options:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
1. Hitting one of the chat-string buttons will take him into chat and starting the chatter with the 
   selected string.

2. Hitting the 'random' button will do the same as abowe, except the it will chose a ransom string.

3. The 'Quiet' button will close the page window and stop flashing screen, but the user will not notice
   anything.
   
4. The 'fuck you' button will kick the user offline. 

5. Closing the pager-window will quit the pager.
 
@endnode
@node "install" ".-^†INSTALLATION†^-."
@next "config"
@prev "how2"
@{b}@{u} Installation: @{ub}@{uu}

Just copy all the included files to the correct dirs. I was to lazy to write an 
installer-script.... :)

Then use the @{"config-editor" link "config" 0} to configure the door for your own needs.
@endnode

@node "config" ".-^ CONFIGURATION ^-."
@prev "install"
@next "thx2"
@{b}@{u} Using the config editor @{ub}@{uu}

On page one you can enter the sentences you want to be able to select from when entering chat.
You can also use some control-commands to include some features like local time/data etc.

The following codes are supported:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%U = Username
%T = Local Time
%D = Date
∂  = will pause the writer for 1/2 second.

On page two you can set if you want the user to write a reason before starting the pager, and you
can also specify a minimum access level to override the chat flag if you are set away.
@endnode
